subject: FW: Moog Updates to LCW Courses
body:
From:
 Grasso, Crystal <cgrasso@moog.com> 
Sent:
 Tuesday, February 28, 2023 4:09 PM
To:
 Grace Vottero <g.vottero@lcwmail.com>
Cc:
 Benton, Chantal <cbenton@moog.com>
Subject:
 Moog Updates to LCW Courses
 
Hi Grace,
 
It was a pleasure meeting you, and I’m looking forward to working with you! Here are a few things I picked up on in two courses that I’d like to see if we can update. I’m happy to get on a call to discuss if you’d like!
 
Introduction to Conscious Inclusion (Unconscious Bias)
In the attached Self Assess Common Microinequities resource guide, could all instances of “microinequities” be changed to “microaggressions”? We are trying to use that term more consistently at Moog now.
In the attached Building and Deepening Relationships resource guide, it mentions “BRGs” but they should be “ERGs”.
 
Fostering Collaboration
On page/slide 8, an example of Janet from Training is used. Could we change Training to Learning and Development? Our training team here is referred to as L&D.
On page/slide 8, can we change the example of utilizing a Team Operating Agreement to "I act collaboratively when I ensure my teammates are aligned on expectations and level of support before starting a new project I'm leading."
On page/slide 9, can we change Training to learning and Development again?
On page/slide 14, it references the DIN model as though it was explained earlier in the video, but I didn’t see that it was. We love the DIN model and would like to figure out how to teach it to employees – I’m thinking we could either explain it in the video or take it out for now and teach employees another way. Do you have any thoughts?
 
Thank you!
 
Thank you,
Crystal
 
Crystal Grasso, MBA, PHR |
 Sr. CG Learning and Development Program Specialist
Moog Human Resources

Grace

 Nassise Geleta <n.geleta@lcwmail.com>; Grace Vottero <g.vottero@lcwmail.com>
Subject:

Hi Nassise and Grace (the extraordinary eLearning editing duo),
 
Thanks for your help with the Conscious Inclusion for All eLearning. Your edits were quite helpful!
 
I’m passing along the leader-level training. Please apply the same vision to this, both on screen and in the read-along text:
Grammatical errors
Spelling errors
Consistency in Capitalization
“J&J” or “Johnson & Johnson” but no other version of the company name
Anything else that seems off
 
Please let me know when you might be able to get to this. It’s not for today, but probably by early next week. Let me know if you have any questions.
 
Thanks!
 
Dan

subject: Point of Contact for Contracts/Agreements
body:
Hi Chuck,
I hope you're having a lovely morning so far!
I'm reaching out with a question about the best point of contact at LCW around our contracts. 
Nicole had been so helpful with this process for our work with Ralph Lauren, which included many reiterations of the contract language. It also included setting up our vendor profile in their systems, which Nicole did and noted that operations would manage. 
I've recently received an email that this system needs updating. Do you know who I should reach out to? Alternatively, I am more than happy to manage this myself for my clients, but would want to be sure to understand who can support with tricky questions. I will also- I believe- need help in resetting the account. Unless Nicole has already shared that account log in info? Their system is Aravo. 
Thank you in advance for your suggestions!
Best,
Grace 
Grace Vottero
(she/her/hers)
Consultant
